Intro

  • Quick Tutorial for using the Flea Flicker Waiver System
  • Start on your team's page.

Click the 'Players' button on the top of the page

Team Page:

Player's Page

Available Players Page:

note: you can sort players here by various columns.
            I sorted by %Owned in other leagues.

Possible Actions:

  • 'Add' a player who is no longer on waivers.
    Note after the waiver period each week (after Weds) players can be picked up at will
  • 'Claim' a player someone dropped:

Possible Actions (cont...):

  • 'Claim' a player who has been put on waivers because they already played this week:
  • Your claims will be processed On Wednesday if they player already played this week or 48 hours after another player drops them.

Example: Claim Matt Jones:

  • Click Claim:

Select a Player on Your Roster to Replace:

  • Note: If you dropped a player without replacing them in an earlier transaction then you do not have to cut anyone in this step.

Drop A Player:

  • Click Radio Button:
  • Click Claim Button:

Are You Sure?: Review Again to Make Sure:

  • At this point it is not submitted until you click Claim
  • Click Claim Button:

Now Adjust Your Bid Amount:

  • Minimum Bid is $0 (Monopoly Money), but if someone bids more for the same player they will get that player instead of you. Bid more for better players.
  • Adjust Your Bid:

Adjust Your Bid (cont...):

  • Click Save:

Change Your Mind Before The Deadline?:

  • Most Waivers process Wednesday Morning, after each week's games. If you decide not to bid on a player after all, then go click the 'X' on the waiver's page to cancel your claim.
  • Cancel:

No Pending Waivers:

  • Since you canceled that claim, now your waiver page shows no pending waivers.
  • Verify No Pending Waivers:
